        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/958977/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-04-01T15:01:38.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Quite a mouthful, both name and wine.<br>\nLight gold color.  The aromas are broad and subtle, with fresh apple, anjou pear, casaba melon and notes of white flowers.  The palate is medium bodied, the fruit a little compressed, but well balanced with good minerality and vibrant acidity.  The finish is moderately long.<br>\nThe second day this is much improved, with gains in both fruit and minerality.  The floral character is unfortunately muted, but the intensity of white fruits and iron minerality is improved, with a much longer finish and more breadth on the palate.<br>\nRated 89.2 the first night, 90.7 tonight.</p>\n<p>Dan Kravitz</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T22:30:25.270Z",
