        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-04-04T14:29:07.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When I was there last year Vincent told me it\u2019s actually Pinot Gouges and Chardonnay. My understanding is that ampelographers will tell you that Pinot Gouges, a white mutant of Pinot Noir propagated by the Gouges family, is actually just a kind of Pinot Blanc, but it\u2019s certainly a high quality selection which cannot be said for a lot of Pinot Blanc out there, so the distinction is worth making.</p>\n<p>I can attest that the 1982 of this cuv\u00e9e is cruising along beautifully.</p>",
